g.text: Github: a public platform for developers which usage
git to upload code , manage , track and collab.
Clone : downloading remote repo's copy in your local computer.
Commit : saving a snapshot of your updated changes.
Branch : copies of your codebase. | where you
can edit/add new code without affecting main
Merge: adding changes from diff. branches
Pull: downloading latest version/changes from remote repo
Push: updating changes to remote repo.
